answersResultList.title: You're a tactful gossip.
answersResultList.resultContent: You don't stick your nose where it doesn't belong, but certain nuggets of information are just too juicy to go unshared. At least you're selective. You trust only those who promise not to tell. You even withhold the worst details if public revelation would crush someone. Still, you'd make a bad conspirator. Avoid a life of crime or politics.

answersResultList.title: You don't gossip.
answersResultList.resultContent: Maybe you're shy, very polite, or just don't care. Maybe knowing glances and whispered comments feel cheap. When personal information comes your way, your lips are sealed. You'd rather talk about current events, literature, or even the weather. People might think you're boring, but if something is none of your business, there's no need to air your opinion about it.
